Classic cupcake in the oven. Ingredients: Butter 175 g, sugar 175 g, chicken egg 3 pcs, wheat flour 240 g, raisins 150 g, vanilla sugar 1 pack, baking powder 0.5 tsp, salt (pinch) to taste. Step-by-step preparation: Eggs and butter should be at room temperature. Put the butter into a deep bowl. Add the regular and vanilla sugar. Beat the mixture with a mixer until fluffy and creamy. Add the eggs one by one. Stir the butter mixture thoroughly each time until smooth. Add the raisins to the bowl. Sift the flour and baking powder through a sieve. Put the batter into the tin.  Bake the cake at 160-180 degrees for about 60-80 minutes until golden brown. 
